annotationA: Cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor subunit 4; Component of the cleavage and polyadenylation specificity factor (CPSF) complex that plays a key role in pre- mRNA 3'-end formation, recognizing the AAUAAA signal sequence and interacting with poly(A) polymerase and other factors to bring about cleavage and poly(A) addition. Has endonuclease activity. Binds RNA polymers with a preference for G- and/or C-rich clusters. Binds single-stranded DNA non-specifically
annotationB: Nucleoporin at 44A, isoform A; Structural constituent of nuclear pore. It is involved in the biological process described with: oogenesis; regulation of mitotic cell cycle; regulation of meiotic cell cycle; Belongs to the WD repeat SEC13 family
